{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17607443","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17607443"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:22:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:22:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15959"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15959","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15959"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.26,0.07,0.07,0.11,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8650"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114793"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8650","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8650"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15959"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96796"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7415"},{"type":"tags","id":"7416"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20706"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114793","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114793"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe inguinal canal is an important anatomical passage through the anterior abdominal wall that extends obliquely from the deep inguinal ring to the superficial inguinal ring.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures forms the floor of the inguinal canal?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Transversus abdominis muscle","Conjoint tendon","Internal oblique muscle","External oblique aponeurosis","Inguinal ligament"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe inguinal canal has four walls and two openings. The \u003Cstrong\u003Einguinal ligament\u003C/strong\u003E forms the inferior wall (floor).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other walls of the inguinal canal are formed by different structures. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal oblique aponeurosis\u003C/strong\u003E forms the anterior wall. The \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal oblique muscle\u003C/strong\u003E forms the superior wall (roof). The \u003Cstrong\u003Etransversus abdominis muscle\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Econjoint tendon\u003C/strong\u003E form the posterior wall. The inguinal canal contains the spermatic cord in men and the round ligament of the uterus in women.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The inguinal canal contains the spermatic cord in men and round ligament in women","The inguinal canal has four walls and two openings (deep and superficial rings)","The contents of the spermatic cord include the vas deferens, testicular vessels, and nerves"],"references":["Last RJ, McMinn RMH, editors. Last\u2019s Anatomy: Regional and Applied. 9th ed. Edinburgh: Churchill Livingstone; 1994; pages 301-304"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96796"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15959"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96796","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96796"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-20T11:49:01+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-20T11:49:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8650"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114793"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null